Solution
The numerator has no zeros, so there is no x-intercept.
The denominator has no real zeros, so there is no
vertical asymptote.
The degree of the numerator, 0, is less than the degree
of the denominator, 2. So, the line y = 0 (the x-axis) is a
horizontal asymptote.
The graph passes through the points (-3, 0.6), (-1, 3),
(0, 6), (1, 3), and (3, 0.6). The domain is all real numbers,
and the range is 0 ≤ y ≤ 6.
